            Title = "Approvals Overview",
            Slug = "approvals-overview",
            Summary = "What the Approvals inbox is, how multi-step approval workflows route requests, and how to approve, reject, or delegate.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/approvals"]""",
            Tags = """["approvals","workflow"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Approvals Overview\n\nThe Approvals module is your personal authorization inbox plus the engine that routes requests through multi-step approval chains. When something needs sign-off — a purchase order, an expense, a quote, a time entry, or a sales order — an approval request lands in the inbox of whoever is responsible for the current step. Approvers review the request and decide: approve it (which advances it to the next step), reject it (which ends it), or delegate it to someone else.\n\n### What Is an Approval Request?\n\nAn approval request is a record that wraps an underlying entity (a PO, expense, etc.) while it moves through an approval workflow. Each request has:\n- An **Entity Type** and **Summary** — what is being approved (e.g., a purchase order number)\n- A link to the **Workflow** that defines the approval chain it follows\n- A **Current Step** — where the request sits in the multi-step chain\n- An optional **Amount** — the financial value (null for non-financial entities like time entries)\n- The **Requested By** name and **Submitted** date\n- A **Status** — Pending, Approved, Rejected, Escalated, Cancelled, or AutoApproved\n- A **decision history** — every approve / reject / delegate / escalate action taken on the request\n\n### The Two Tabs\n\nThe Approvals page has two tabs:\n\n1. **Inbox** — Everyone's personal queue of pending requests awaiting their decision. This is the default tab and is available to all users.\n2. **Workflows** — The workflow definition editor, visible only to Admins and Managers. This is where you configure which entity types trigger approvals and how the approval chain is built.\n\n### How Multi-Step Approvals Work\n\n1. **Definition** — An Admin or Manager defines a workflow with one or more sequential steps. Each step names an approver (a specific user, a role, or the requester's manager) and optional conditions.\n2. **Activation** — When an entity is submitted, the system matches it to an active workflow for that entity type, optionally honoring an amount threshold (e.g., only POs over $500 require approval).\n3. **Step progression** — The request starts at Step 1. The assigned approver reviews it and decides.\n4. **Routing on decision:**\n   - **Approve** → advances to the next step, or completes the request if it was the final step\n   - **Reject** → the request is terminal (Rejected); rejections require a reason/comment\n   - **Delegate** → hands the decision to another user, still at the same step\n   - **Escalate** → typically automatic when a step sits pending past its escalation window\n5. **Completion** — Once the final step is approved, the request becomes Approved and a completion timestamp is recorded.\n\n### Thresholds and Automation\n\n- **Activation threshold** — A workflow can require approval only above a dollar amount; smaller requests skip the workflow entirely.\n- **Auto-approve below** — A step can auto-approve when the request amount is under a configured value, so trivial amounts don't tie up an approver. These requests show as AutoApproved.\n- **Escalate after (hours)** — A step can auto-escalate if it sits pending longer than the configured number of hours, so requests don't stall.\n\n### Approver Assignment\n\nEach step assigns an approver by type:\n- **Specific User** — the request goes to one named person\n- **Role** — the request goes to anyone holding that role (Admin, Manager, Office Manager, or PM)\n- **Manager** — the request goes to the requester's direct manager\n\n### When to Use Approvals\n\n- When you're an approver — check the Inbox tab to act on requests waiting on you\n- When a purchase order, expense, quote, time entry, or sales order needs sign-off before it proceeds\n- When you (Admin/Manager) need to define or adjust the approval chain for an entity type\n- When you need an audit trail of who approved, rejected, or delegated a request and when","sections":[]}"""
        });

