            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/approvals","startButtonLabel":"Tour Approvals","steps":[{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"Inbox and Workflows Tabs","description":"The Approvals page has two tabs. Inbox is your personal queue of pending requests waiting on your decision and is available to everyone. Workflows is the approval-chain editor, visible only to Admins and Managers. Click a tab to switch; the active tab is reflected in the URL.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"app-data-table[tableId='approval-inbox']","popover":{"title":"Approval Inbox Queue","description":"Every request awaiting your decision appears here. Columns show the Entity Type and Summary (what is being approved), the Workflow name, the current Approval Step, the Amount, who Requested it, and when it was Submitted. The Amount shows a dash for non-financial entities like time entries.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table[tableId='approval-inbox']","popover":{"title":"Approve a Request","description":"Each row in the inbox carries a green Approve button in its Actions column. Click Approve to accept that request at the current step. If this was the final step, the request completes and is marked Approved; otherwise it advances to the next approver in the chain. No reason is required to approve.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table[tableId='approval-inbox']","popover":{"title":"Reject a Request","description":"Next to each row's Approve button is a red Reject icon. Click it to open the rejection dialog. Rejecting requires a reason — type your explanation in the comments field (up to 1000 characters) and confirm. A rejected request is terminal and will not advance.","side":"top"}},{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"Switch to Workflows (Admin / Manager)","description":"If you're an Admin or Manager, click the Workflows tab to define how requests are routed. This is where you decide which entity types require approval and how many steps each approval chain has.","side":