            AppRoutes = """["/approvals"]""",
            Tags = """["approvals","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Approvals — Advanced Reference\n\nEdge-case and power-user notes for the Approvals module. Everything here sits beyond the core inbox/workflow flows: how requests are born, where the data model exposes more than the UI does today, and how write permissions split between Admin and Manager. The whole controller is gated by the **CAP-P2P-APPROVALS** capability — disable it and every endpoint returns 403.\n\n## How an Entity Enters the Inbox\n\nRequests are not created by hand. An entity reaches an approver's inbox only after its owning feature calls the submit endpoint:\n\n- **`POST /api/v1/approvals/submit`** — body `{ entityType, entityId, amount?, entitySummary? }`. The server matches the entity against the **active** workflow registered for that `entityType` (PurchaseOrder, Expense, Quote, TimeEntry, SalesOrder). One active workflow per entity type is the practical model.\n- **Threshold matching.** A workflow stores its activation rule as `activationConditionsJson`, e.g. `{\"amountGreaterThan\": 500}`. The editor surfaces this as the single **Amount Threshold** field. If the submitted `amount` does not clear the threshold, no request is created and the endpoint returns **`{ approvalRequired: false }`** (HTTP 200, not 201) — the calling feature treats that as \"proceed, no sign-off needed.\"\n- **Created vs. skipped.** When a workflow matches and the threshold is cleared, the request is created at Step 1 and the endpoint returns **201 Created** with a `Location` header. The decision history starts empty.\n- **Inbox query.** `GET /api/v1/approvals/pending` returns only requests whose current step resolves to the calling user (by Specific User, Role membership, or being the requester's direct Manager). The inbox is server-filtered per user; there is no \"all requests\" view in the UI.\n\n## Model-vs-UI Gaps\n\nSeveral capabilities exist in the API and the data model but are **not wired into the screen** today. Know these so you don't promise a button that isn't there.\n\n- **Delegation — API only.** `POST /api/v1/approvals/{requestId}/delegate` (body `{ delegateToUserId, comments? }`) and the `ApprovalsService.delegate()` client method both exist, and each step carries an `allowDelegation` flag (defaults true). But the inbox renders only **Approve** and **Reject** — there is no Delegate button. `Delegate` is a valid decision type in the history model; it just can't be triggered from the current UI.\n- **History — API only.** `GET /api/v1/approvals/history/{entityType}/{entityId}` and `getApprovalHistory()` return the full decision trail, and the `ApprovalRequest.decisions[]` array (each with `decision`, `decidedByName`, `comments`, `delegatedToUserName`, `decidedAt`) ships on every request. No component renders that timeline yet — the inbox loads `pending` only.\n- **Active toggle — read-only in UI.** A workflow's `isActive` flag shows in the list as an **Active / Inactive** chip, but the workflow editor form has **no toggle** for it. There is no UI path to deactivate a workflow without deleting it; flipping `isActive` is a model/API concern.\n- **Delete — API only.** `DELETE /api/v1/approvals/workflows/{id}` exists (Admin-only, soft delete), but the workflow list's Actions column carries **only an edit (pencil) icon** — no delete action, and `ApprovalsService` has no `deleteWorkflow()` method. The trash icon in the editor removes a **step**, not the workflow.\n- **Per-step fields without controls.** Each step's payload includes `requireComments` (default false) and `allowDelegation` (default true). They are sent on save and honored server-side, but the step editor exposes no inputs for them — they ride along at their defaults.\n\n## Admin-vs-Manager Write Split\n\nThe Workflows tab is visible to both Admin and Manager, but **only Admin can write**:\n\n- **`GET /workflows`** — `[Authorize(Roles = \"Admin,Manager\")]`. Both roles can list and open workflows.\n- **`POST /workflows`**, **`PUT /workflows/{id}`**, **`DELETE /workflows/{id}`** — `[Authorize(Roles = \"Admin\")]`. Manager calls are rejected with **403**.\n- **UI consequence.** The client gate `canManageWorkflows` returns true for Admin **or** Manager, so a Manager sees the Workflows tab, the New Workflow button, and the editor — but any save/create/delete they attempt fails server-side with 403 (surfaced as an access-denied snackbar). Treat Managers as read-only on workflow definitions; only Admins author the approval chains. Inbox actions (approve/reject/delegate) are not role-gated beyond the capability — any assigned approver can act on their own queue.\n","sections":[]}"""
        });

